From: Soren Brinkmann <soren.brinkmann@xilinx.com>
Date: Tue, 30 Apr 2013 10:40:31 -0700
Subject: [PATCH 349/628] gpio: xgpiops: Fix interrupts for banks > 0

git://github.com/Xilinx/linux-xlnx.git xilinx-v14.7
commit ca2d4f14bf5e5943cd09776cee4a7e1a4d57f400

The way IRQ numbers were calculated for banks greater than zero was
wrong resulting in a BUG.

Reported-by: Hafner Michael <hafner.michael@heidenhain.de>
Signed-off-by: Soren Brinkmann <soren.brinkmann@xilinx.com>
Signed-off-by: Michal Simek <michal.simek@xilinx.com>
Signed-off-by: Liming Wang <liming.wang@windriver.com>
---
 drivers/gpio/gpio-xilinxps.c |    3 +--
 1 files changed, 1 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/gpio/gpio-xilinxps.c b/drivers/gpio/gpio-xilinxps.c
index 8c51700..f94ade2 100644
--- a/drivers/gpio/gpio-xilinxps.c
+++ b/drivers/gpio/gpio-xilinxps.c
@@ -426,8 +426,7 @@ static void xgpiops_irqhandler(unsigned int irq, struct irq_desc *desc)
 			generic_handle_irq(gpio_irq);
 		}
 		/* shift to first virtual irq of next bank */
-		gpio_irq = (int)irq_get_handler_data(irq) +
-				(xgpiops_pin_table[bank_num] + 1);
+		gpio_irq = gpio->irq_base + xgpiops_pin_table[bank_num] + 1;
 	}
 
 	chip = irq_desc_get_chip(desc);
-- 
